snippet.textDisplay: "There are huge differences in performance and capabilities between the XSX and PS5".  How can you say that when we're several months from these machines shipping and you haven't played any of the games for them?  Exaggerating the difference in the GPU's which isn't really that much.  Comparing teraflops which Digital Foundry already pointed out is irrelevant.  Underselling the speed of the PS5 SSD.  And the real cherry on top, spinning MS' proprietary SSD expansion as a "feature".  No one is going to need a SSD expansion until at least a year after launch when off the shelf products compatible with PS5 will be available and likely much cheaper than MS' expansion cards.
